01:17.584 --> 01:21.375
- [VOICEOVER] Tag,
you're it, Elizabeth.

01:22.042 --> 01:25.542
(RUSTLING LEAVES)

01:36.250 --> 01:39.792
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:52.000 --> 01:55.959
- I wonder where little
girls go when they die.

01:56.792 --> 02:00.042
(BREEZY RUSTLING)

02:11.000 --> 02:14.542
(BLOOD-CURDLING SCREAM)

02:14.584 --> 02:17.959
- [VOICEOVER] Elizabeth,
what have you done?!

02:20.792 --> 02:22.250
- You said it was my day.

02:24.209 --> 02:25.958
Anything I wanted.

02:25.959 --> 02:27.209
(BLOOD-CURDLING SCREAM)

02:27.375 --> 02:30.792
(VACUUM MOTOR)

02:35.959 --> 02:39.250
(HEAVY SIGH)

02:39.292 --> 02:41.092
- I swear, you are such
a little hair factory.

02:41.125 --> 02:44.834
Between you and Ben, I'm never
gonna get this house clean.

02:45.501 --> 02:48.959
Well, don't mind me.

02:50.542 --> 02:52.042
(SCREAMS)
(RATTLE)

02:53.959 --> 02:56.542
- Damn it, Ben, you
scared the crap out of me.

02:56.876 --> 02:59.958
Now what?

02:59.959 --> 03:01.958
- It's everything, Stacey.

03:01.959 --> 03:03.958
You, that dog.

03:03.959 --> 03:05.959
Everything is out of order,

03:06.042 --> 03:07.918
out of its place.

03:07.959 --> 03:10.667
Let me show you again.

03:14.959 --> 03:18.667
Everything must be
stacked perfectly

03:18.709 --> 03:21.334
with exactly one
pinky's-width betwen each row.

03:21.375 --> 03:24.958
Your pinkies are
smaller than mine

03:24.959 --> 03:26.709
so you'll have to
adjust for that.

03:26.751 --> 03:29.918
Got it?

03:29.959 --> 03:32.958
- Maybe this will work.

03:32.959 --> 03:34.751
- Anyway, I fixed it this time

03:34.792 --> 03:36.918
but please, be more
thoughtful in the future.

03:36.959 --> 03:40.125
- You know, you're amazing.

03:40.167 --> 03:41.626
Not a single can out of place

03:41.667 --> 03:43.226
but you can't lift a single
finger to help clean the house.

03:43.250 --> 03:45.876
- My house, my dirt.

03:45.918 --> 03:47.417
- Thought it was Mom's house?

03:47.459 --> 03:48.626
- Was.

03:48.667 --> 03:51.958
- Ben, you've
gotta be realistic.

03:51.959 --> 03:53.351
I can't stay here forever and
just keep taking care of...

03:53.375 --> 03:56.125
- No one is asking you to.

03:56.167 --> 03:58.209
- Ben, you gotta learn
to take care of yourself

03:58.250 --> 04:00.959
or go somewhere
someone else can.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.834
If you would just let
me try a little bit

04:04.876 --> 04:06.351
of behavioral therapy, I
know that I would be...

04:06.375 --> 04:08.167
- Don't analyze me!

04:08.209 --> 04:10.626
I'm not one of
your case studies.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.959
Now, please, keep that
slobber bucket away from me.

04:13.626 --> 04:16.834
(SIGH)

04:16.875 --> 04:20.083
(DOG BARKS)

04:20.125 --> 04:22.958
(LAUGHS)
- Good boy.

04:22.959 --> 04:23.959
(STOMPING)

04:24.000 --> 04:25.334
Oh, what are we
gonna do with him?

04:26.667 --> 04:28.417
The Caged Family by
Stacey Lynch, PHD,

04:30.751 --> 04:34.042
RESEARCH, CHAPTER ONE:

04:34.083 --> 04:36.125
(SIGH)
Subject has OCD

04:36.167 --> 04:39.125
and multiple phobias,
the most severe of which

04:39.167 --> 04:41.417
is agoraphobia.

04:41.459 --> 04:42.852
Subject has been unable
to leave his house

04:42.876 --> 04:44.542
for 23 years.

04:45.417 --> 04:49.209
Not even to attend
his mother's funeral.

04:50.125 --> 04:53.959
Uh, that's pretty
screwed-up isn't it, boy?

04:54.000 --> 04:56.584
Hmm?

04:56.626 --> 04:58.209
What are we gonna do with him?

04:58.250 --> 05:01.958
Well, I don't know but
we're gonna have to try

05:01.959 --> 05:04.334
to fix him.

05:04.375 --> 05:05.542
But for now, we need a break.

05:05.584 --> 05:08.292
Come on, that's a good boy.

05:08.334 --> 05:10.751
(JAZZY TRUMPET MUSIC)
♪ Let's dance,

05:10.792 --> 05:12.459
♪ Oh, yeah

05:12.501 --> 05:14.292
♪ I'm gonna dance with Duke

05:14.334 --> 05:16.042
(SCAT SINGING)

05:18.000 --> 05:20.250
(LIPS SMACKING)
(LAUGHING)

05:22.667 --> 05:25.000
(DEEP SIGH)

05:28.959 --> 05:32.292
Who want's to play ball?

05:32.334 --> 05:34.334
Go get your ball.

05:34.375 --> 05:35.584
Go get your ball.

05:35.959 --> 05:39.292
(SQUEAK)
Gimme your ball.

05:39.334 --> 05:41.292
That's a good boy.

05:41.334 --> 05:42.709
(DOG GROANS)

05:42.751 --> 05:44.834
(SQUEAKING)

05:49.959 --> 05:53.125
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

05:57.959 --> 06:01.125
(DOG CRIES)

06:14.709 --> 06:18.042
(DARK, EVOCATIVE MUSIC)

06:28.959 --> 06:32.209
(RUSTLING LEAVES)

06:33.125 --> 06:36.459
(DOG BARKS)

06:36.501 --> 06:39.459
Alright, already.

06:43.000 --> 06:46.334
(DOG BARKS)

06:46.375 --> 06:47.209
Duke!

06:47.250 --> 06:48.959
I just swept this porch.

06:49.375 --> 06:52.751
You better run.

06:52.792 --> 06:55.083
(SQUEAKING)
Come on.

06:55.125 --> 06:57.334
Bring it here.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.292
Come on, baby.

06:59.334 --> 07:00.501
Come on, bring it here.

07:00.542 --> 07:02.959
(SQUEAKING)

07:03.042 --> 07:05.959
(THREATENING MUSIC)

07:08.375 --> 07:10.125
- This is not OK!

07:11.876 --> 07:14.459
Get it off!

07:17.209 --> 07:20.459
(FOOTSTEPS)

07:20.501 --> 07:21.876
(RATTLING AND KNOCKING)

07:25.959 --> 07:29.334
(SLOSHY FOOTSTEPS)

07:33.959 --> 07:37.250
(DOG PANTING)

07:49.959 --> 07:53.375
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

08:01.959 --> 08:05.459
- No, not the dirt!

08:05.501 --> 08:07.185
Get in this house right
now, Benjamin Lynch.

08:07.209 --> 08:08.976
You filthy little boy,
you'll catch your death.

08:09.000 --> 08:11.958
- No, Mama.

08:11.959 --> 08:12.976
- It's none of your concern.

08:13.000 --> 08:15.334
(FOOTSTEPS)

08:23.751 --> 08:26.959
- Ow.

08:31.125 --> 08:34.542
Mommy, it burns.

08:36.751 --> 08:38.501
(WATER DRIPPING)

08:41.000 --> 08:42.958
Mommy, you're hurting me.

08:44.667 --> 08:46.959
- Now there's my
sweet, clean son.

08:56.751 --> 08:59.959
(RUBBING)

09:32.292 --> 09:35.792
(THREATENING MUSIC)

09:35.834 --> 09:39.209
- My coconut water
supply is depleted.

09:39.250 --> 09:42.083
You were supposed to
buy more yesterday.

09:42.125 --> 09:44.751
- What are you talking about,

09:44.792 --> 09:45.958
there's like 20
bottles in there?

09:45.959 --> 09:47.334
- Those are for my smoothies.

09:47.375 --> 09:48.709
You know that.

09:48.751 --> 09:49.958
You have to go to the store now.

09:49.959 --> 09:52.059
What if the weather is bad
tomorrow or the car won't start?

09:52.083 --> 09:54.958
Anything could happen.

09:54.959 --> 09:56.958
It must be stocked now or
I won't be able to sleep.

09:56.959 --> 09:59.209
- I'm not doing it.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.958
I'm not driving 20 miles
to buy you the same thing

10:00.959 --> 10:03.334
you already have.

10:03.375 --> 10:05.334
Drink the left side
waters, please.

10:05.375 --> 10:07.958
- Fine.

10:07.959 --> 10:09.167
I'll just dehydrate then.

10:09.209 --> 10:11.042
You're so selfish.

10:11.083 --> 10:12.459
- Selfish?

10:12.501 --> 10:13.959
I dropped everything
to come here.

10:14.042 --> 10:16.959
My practice is hemorrhaging
money so I can be your maid

10:17.000 --> 10:19.958
and plan a funeral for a
woman I couldn't stand.

10:19.959 --> 10:23.083
- And there's another thing,

10:23.125 --> 10:25.459
I asked you to put fresh flowers
at her grave two days ago.

10:25.959 --> 10:29.501
- Would you look at yourself?

10:29.542 --> 10:31.834
You don't have a
life because of Mom.

10:31.876 --> 10:34.958
How can you still care
about that crazy woman?

10:34.959 --> 10:37.958
- She wasn't crazy.

10:37.959 --> 10:40.125
She felt things,
she knew things.

10:40.167 --> 10:42.375
- She knew how to control you.

10:42.417 --> 10:44.334
- She just wanted us to be safe.

10:44.375 --> 10:46.626
You never understood her or me.

10:46.667 --> 10:48.959
You left the first
chance you got.

10:49.042 --> 10:50.959
(OMINOUS MUSIC)
Please, Stacey,

10:51.000 --> 10:52.958
she's our mother.

10:52.959 --> 10:55.459
I'd take them myself if I could.

10:56.709 --> 10:58.959
- Alright, I'll do it.
(SIGHS)

11:03.959 --> 11:07.876
(HEAVY BREATHING)
Just so you know,

11:07.918 --> 11:10.709
I'm not doing this for you.

11:10.751 --> 11:12.501
I'm doing it for Ben.

11:13.083 --> 11:16.958
You know, you really
screwed him up.

11:16.959 --> 11:18.959
And you were OK with it

11:19.042 --> 11:20.542
because as long as he was sick,

11:20.584 --> 11:21.959
he was never gonna leave you.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.727
But guess what, now you're
gone, and he's alone.

11:23.751 --> 11:25.958
And now, he doesn't have
the life he deserves.

11:25.959 --> 11:28.209
But, you know what Mom,
I am gonna change that

11:28.250 --> 11:30.501
and give it to him.

11:30.542 --> 11:32.958
(RUSTLING LEAVES)

11:32.959 --> 11:34.959
(DOG GROANING)

11:39.959 --> 11:43.209
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

11:43.959 --> 11:47.334
- Stacey, are you OK?

11:47.375 --> 11:50.042
- I haven't felt
this good in years.

11:50.083 --> 11:51.584
(CLAP)
Coconut water's on me.

11:51.626 --> 11:53.167
(DOG GROWLING)

11:53.209 --> 11:53.959
- Ah, get him off me!

11:54.000 --> 11:55.958
- Come on, Duke.

11:55.959 --> 11:56.959
Come on, boy, let's go.

11:57.000 --> 11:58.083
Outside, outside.

11:58.125 --> 11:59.167
What are you doing?

11:59.209 --> 12:00.083
Come on, let's get outside.

12:00.125 --> 12:00.959
Duke, come with me.

12:01.000 --> 12:02.667
Duke, this way.

12:02.709 --> 12:03.958
Come on now, Ben's
not in the mood.

12:03.959 --> 12:05.417
Let's go outside, good boy.

12:05.459 --> 12:06.876
That's a good boy, come on.

12:09.209 --> 12:12.417
(GASP)

12:12.459 --> 12:14.959
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

12:27.667 --> 12:30.958
That's a good boy.

12:30.959 --> 12:32.501
- Do you see what he has done?

12:32.542 --> 12:34.918
He digs and he digs

12:34.959 --> 12:36.250
and he brings the outside in.

12:36.292 --> 12:38.667
Look at this!

12:38.709 --> 12:39.959
- I'm sorry, he's a dog.

12:40.042 --> 12:41.709
That's what dogs do.

12:41.751 --> 12:43.268
- From now on, he
stays out of the house.

12:43.292 --> 12:46.042
The hair, the digging, the dirt.

12:46.667 --> 12:49.876
No more.

12:49.918 --> 12:50.976
- We'll talk about this
when you've calmed down.

12:51.000 --> 12:54.292
(DOG BARKS)
Hey, settle down, boy.

12:54.334 --> 12:56.958
Hey, hey, hey.

12:56.959 --> 12:58.958
Settle down, boy, settle down.

12:58.959 --> 13:00.959
Come on, let's go.

13:01.042 --> 13:01.959
Outside, outside.

13:02.000 --> 13:03.083
Duke, come on.

13:03.125 --> 13:03.959
Let's go, this way.

13:04.000 --> 13:05.417
What are you doing?

13:05.459 --> 13:06.667
Come here, boy.

13:06.709 --> 13:07.501
Let's go outside.

13:07.542 --> 13:08.667
Settle down.

13:08.709 --> 13:09.375
Come on, let's go.

13:09.417 --> 13:10.083
Outside, outside.

13:10.125 --> 13:12.209
Duke, come on.

13:12.250 --> 13:13.250
Come on, get outside.

13:13.292 --> 13:14.292
Come on.

13:17.334 --> 13:20.709
Come on, Duke.

13:20.751 --> 13:21.792
Alright, here we go.

13:21.834 --> 13:24.417
(HEAVY BREATHING)
What has gotten in to you?

13:24.459 --> 13:26.959
Whew, I thought you had a
higher tolerance for assholes.

13:27.709 --> 13:31.626
You're just gonna have
to stay out here for now.

13:31.667 --> 13:34.751
Not that I wouldn't be
fine with you eating him

13:34.792 --> 13:37.834
but he'd probably just
give you a tummy ache.

13:38.083 --> 13:41.626
Alright, you be good.

13:41.667 --> 13:43.167
You stay out here.

13:43.209 --> 13:46.209
- I've had enough.

13:46.250 --> 13:47.042
He's got to go.

13:47.083 --> 13:48.602
- We've been here for two
weeks without any trouble.

13:48.626 --> 13:49.958
He's just acting out
because you're so hostile.

13:49.959 --> 13:51.958
It'll pass.

13:51.959 --> 13:53.059
- Acting out or
not, I don't care.

13:53.083 --> 13:54.958
He goes!

13:54.959 --> 13:56.226
- Come on, you have to
give him another chance.

13:56.250 --> 13:58.584
- He can stay outside.

13:58.626 --> 14:00.501
But you have to
clean my comforter.

14:00.542 --> 14:01.958
And I mean cleaned.

14:01.959 --> 14:03.459
Boiling water and bleach.

14:06.000 --> 14:07.000
(FOOTSTEPS)

14:18.125 --> 14:21.501
- Ah, that dog.

14:21.542 --> 14:24.083
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

14:28.959 --> 14:32.250
(CREAKING)

14:32.292 --> 14:34.959
Creepy.

14:35.584 --> 14:38.959
(DOG BARKING)

14:40.959 --> 14:41.959
- Stupid dog.

14:49.083 --> 14:52.334
(CREAK)

14:58.709 --> 15:01.918
(SLAM)

15:01.959 --> 15:03.667
(STARTLED CRY)

15:03.709 --> 15:05.477
- Damn it, Ben, you
scared the crap out of me.

15:05.501 --> 15:08.958
- I need my coconut water.

15:08.959 --> 15:10.667
(SIGH)
- Stop creepin' around.

15:10.709 --> 15:14.042
- [BEN] I need my coconut water.

15:14.083 --> 15:17.125
(SIGH)

15:17.167 --> 15:20.042
- Fine.

15:20.083 --> 15:22.250
Excuse me.

15:26.334 --> 15:29.834
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

15:29.876 --> 15:31.918
Hey.

15:31.959 --> 15:34.083
Hey, don't worry, buddy.

15:34.125 --> 15:36.626
Everything's gonna be OK.

15:36.667 --> 15:39.250
Yeah.
(BARK)

15:39.292 --> 15:40.125
OK, alright, honey.

15:40.167 --> 15:42.250
You just behave
until I get back.

15:42.292 --> 15:44.292
Mom will bring you a treat, OK?

15:44.334 --> 15:46.334
(LIPS SMACK)
Alright, be a good boy.

15:59.959 --> 16:03.042
- No.

16:03.083 --> 16:05.375
No, no, little girl.

16:06.209 --> 16:09.959
You're gonna get
yourself killed.

16:14.209 --> 16:17.459
What?

16:19.959 --> 16:23.459
(BARKING AND SNARLING)

16:27.542 --> 16:28.542
(BARKING)

16:36.459 --> 16:39.792
(SNARLING)

17:02.083 --> 17:05.291
What?!

17:05.334 --> 17:06.584
(BARKING)

17:06.626 --> 17:08.459
What do you want?!

17:09.584 --> 17:12.959
(CREEPY MUSIC)

17:13.083 --> 17:16.501
What the Hell?

17:35.042 --> 17:38.250
Shit!

17:38.292 --> 17:39.959
(GROWLING AND BARKING)

17:41.792 --> 17:43.959
(BARKING)

17:46.501 --> 17:49.918
(INTENSE MUSIC)

17:52.542 --> 17:54.626
Damn It, Stacey,
it's not a barn.

17:56.751 --> 17:59.959
(BARKING)

18:02.542 --> 18:04.876
(FOOTSTEPS)

18:05.918 --> 18:08.959
(RATTLE)

18:10.209 --> 18:11.209
(HEAVY BREATHING)

18:31.250 --> 18:34.626
One for me,

18:36.209 --> 18:38.167
and one for Duke.

18:41.918 --> 18:43.250
(BARKING)

18:46.751 --> 18:48.792
Make it two.

19:04.459 --> 19:07.792
(CLANGING)

19:20.584 --> 19:23.958
(BARKING AND GROWLING)

19:23.959 --> 19:25.792
(GRUNTING)

19:31.959 --> 19:35.542
(PANICKED GROANS)
(SNARLING)

19:42.959 --> 19:46.167
(RATTLING)

19:46.209 --> 19:48.918
(HEAVY BREATHING)

19:48.959 --> 19:50.959
(SLAM)
(SNARLING)

19:51.042 --> 19:54.000
(SCRATCHING)

20:10.125 --> 20:13.334
(SIGH)

20:13.375 --> 20:16.959
(HEAVY BREATHING)
Good boy.

20:17.959 --> 20:21.125
(SCRATCHING)

20:21.167 --> 20:24.417
(BARKING AND SNARLING)

20:28.959 --> 20:29.959
Oh, shit.

20:36.042 --> 20:39.375
(KNOCKING)

20:39.876 --> 20:42.958
(SLAM)

20:42.959 --> 20:43.959
(BARKING)

20:44.501 --> 20:47.959
(SNARLING AND SCRATCHING)

20:56.501 --> 20:59.918
(PHONE RINGING)

21:00.209 --> 21:03.417
- Hello.

21:03.459 --> 21:04.958
- Stacey, your dog...
(GUTTURAL VOICE)

21:04.959 --> 21:08.501
Stacey!
(GUTTURAL VOICE)

21:08.542 --> 21:11.167
Sta...!
(GUTTURAL VOICE)

21:11.209 --> 21:12.542
(ANGUISHED GROAN)

21:12.584 --> 21:13.417
- Hello?

21:13.459 --> 21:14.459
(BUSY SIGNAL)

21:14.959 --> 21:18.209
Jesus.
(MUMBLES)

21:18.250 --> 21:21.417
(CAR ENGINE)

21:34.167 --> 21:37.709
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

21:44.417 --> 21:47.626
Ben?

21:47.959 --> 21:50.959
Duke?!

21:51.250 --> 21:53.459
Duke?!

21:54.501 --> 21:56.958
Ben?!

21:56.959 --> 21:58.125
(GROWL)

21:58.167 --> 22:00.375
Duke?

22:00.417 --> 22:01.417
(BARKING AND SNARLING)

22:01.584 --> 22:04.958
What's wrong, boy?

22:04.959 --> 22:06.125
(BARKING AND SNARLING)

22:07.000 --> 22:10.334
OK, stop it.

22:10.375 --> 22:11.709
Duke, stop it right now!

22:11.751 --> 22:13.626
(GROWLING)

22:14.584 --> 22:18.375
- [BEN] Stacey,
something's wrong with him!

22:18.417 --> 22:21.167
(SNARLING AND BARKING)

22:21.959 --> 22:25.375
(PANICKED YELPS)

22:36.083 --> 22:39.667
(BARKING AND SNARLING)

22:47.083 --> 22:50.584
- [BEN] Duke, no!

22:59.250 --> 23:02.834
(SNARLING AND BARKING)

23:06.167 --> 23:07.918
(PANICKED YELPS)

23:15.292 --> 23:18.667
- Oh my, God.

23:18.709 --> 23:20.292
(BARKING AND SNARLING)

23:48.167 --> 23:51.667
(HEAVY BREATHING)

23:53.918 --> 23:56.501
(PHONE RINGING)

23:57.083 --> 24:00.125
Ben, is that you?
(GUTTURAL VOICE)

24:01.667 --> 24:04.209
(GUTTURAL VOICE)

24:08.959 --> 24:12.334
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

24:35.626 --> 24:38.959
(HEAVY BREATHING)

24:45.083 --> 24:48.375
(TAPPING)

24:48.417 --> 24:50.125
Ben, it's me.

24:50.167 --> 24:51.334
Open up.

24:51.375 --> 24:52.501
Open the door.

24:55.959 --> 24:58.958
Ben.

24:58.959 --> 25:01.125
Let me in.

25:01.876 --> 25:04.959
- Where is he?

25:05.042 --> 25:06.125
- I don't know.

25:06.167 --> 25:07.167
He's out back somewhere.

25:07.209 --> 25:08.969
- Something is seriously
wrong with that dog.

25:09.000 --> 25:10.958
(PANTING)
- I don't know, he just...

25:10.959 --> 25:12.185
He must be injured
or sick or something.

25:12.209 --> 25:14.958
I don't know, he's never done
anything like this before.

25:14.959 --> 25:17.958
I mean, he doesn't
even chase squirrels.

25:17.959 --> 25:19.334
- He's not normal.

25:19.375 --> 25:20.852
I fed him two Xanax and
he's more vicious than ever.

25:20.876 --> 25:22.959
- What?!

25:23.042 --> 25:24.125
You drugged my dog?

25:24.167 --> 25:25.958
How dare you?!

25:25.959 --> 25:27.768
I mean, he just probably had
a bad reaction or something.

25:27.792 --> 25:29.958
- He tried to kill me.

25:29.959 --> 25:31.477
- [STACEY] Oh my, God.
- Xanax doesn't do that.

25:31.501 --> 25:34.125
(HEAVY BREATHING)
I'm calling Animal Control.

25:34.167 --> 25:36.667
- What?!

25:36.709 --> 25:37.751
No!

25:37.792 --> 25:39.584
He's just sick!

25:42.542 --> 25:43.584
- Stacey, don't be a fool.

25:45.959 --> 25:48.958
- Screw you, Ben.

25:48.959 --> 25:52.125
(SHORT PANICKED BREATHS)

25:56.959 --> 26:00.375
(HEAVY BREATHING)

26:16.959 --> 26:20.209
Where did he go?

26:20.250 --> 26:22.292
- With any luck, off to die.

26:22.334 --> 26:24.054
- You just can't help
being a dick, can you?

26:25.375 --> 26:28.918
I have to find him.

26:29.751 --> 26:32.959
(EERIE MUSIC)

26:38.417 --> 26:41.626
Run.

26:43.959 --> 26:47.042
(GASPING)

26:47.083 --> 26:50.083
(SQUEAK)

26:52.334 --> 26:54.375
(PADDING)

26:56.792 --> 27:00.292
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)
Close the door.

27:00.334 --> 27:03.751
(GROWLING)

27:03.792 --> 27:06.958
No, Duke.

27:06.959 --> 27:08.792
(BARKING)

27:08.834 --> 27:10.958
Duke, stay.

27:10.959 --> 27:12.375
(SNARLING AND BARKING)

27:12.417 --> 27:15.209
No.

27:15.250 --> 27:17.167
Duke, please.

27:17.209 --> 27:19.958
Please don't.

27:19.959 --> 27:21.876
(SNARLING AND BARKING)

27:21.918 --> 27:24.834
Oh, Duke, please.

27:24.876 --> 27:27.292
Please...
(WHIMPERING)

27:27.334 --> 27:30.334
(SNARLING)

27:30.375 --> 27:33.709
(ANGUISHED YELL)
(CRACK)

27:34.542 --> 27:37.959
(RATTLING AND CLATTER)

27:43.542 --> 27:46.792
(SLAM)

27:48.334 --> 27:49.334
Oh my, God, Duke.

27:51.834 --> 27:52.958
I'm so sorry.

27:52.959 --> 27:54.042
Ben!

27:54.083 --> 27:55.167
(CRYING)
Ben, help me!

27:55.209 --> 27:57.167
(CRYING)
Oh, Duke, I'm so sorry.

27:57.209 --> 28:00.459
What is going on?

28:00.501 --> 28:01.959
Ben!

28:02.042 --> 28:05.209
Help me!
(CRYING)

28:06.000 --> 28:09.375
(FOOTSTEPS)

28:27.250 --> 28:30.584
- Is he OK?

28:30.626 --> 28:33.959
- I don't know.

28:34.334 --> 28:37.751
- The collar.

28:38.751 --> 28:42.125
- I had to leave it there.

28:42.167 --> 28:45.083
- Will they let
you stay with him?

28:45.125 --> 28:47.459
They should.

28:47.501 --> 28:49.018
I'll take care of things
until you get back.

28:49.042 --> 28:51.542
- You take care of things?

28:51.584 --> 28:53.958
You left me there.

28:53.959 --> 28:57.209
- I didn't mean to.

28:57.250 --> 28:59.459
I froze.

28:59.501 --> 29:01.584
- You weren't too frozen to run!

29:01.626 --> 29:05.584
("THE BREATH AND THE
PROMISE" BY JAMES BEAUREGARD)

29:20.626 --> 29:23.959
(SNIFFLING)

29:29.542 --> 29:32.834
(KNOCKING)

29:32.876 --> 29:34.959
Go away.

29:41.709 --> 29:45.209
- Just for me to say I'm sorry.

29:49.751 --> 29:53.042
- Is there Xanax in it?

29:53.083 --> 29:55.501
- No.

29:55.542 --> 29:58.876
- Can I have one?

30:06.083 --> 30:09.459
Make it two.

30:37.959 --> 30:41.375
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

30:44.417 --> 30:46.459
(CREEPY OMINOUS MUSIC)

30:50.918 --> 30:52.083
(TICKING CLOCK)

30:58.542 --> 31:01.958
(BARKING)
(SCREAM)

31:01.959 --> 31:05.125
(INTENSELY DRAMATIC MUSIC)

31:15.959 --> 31:19.584
(MUFFLED, ANGUISHED CRIES)

31:35.959 --> 31:39.375
(PANICKED GASP)

31:39.834 --> 31:42.958
(SLAM)

31:42.959 --> 31:44.959
(BREEZY RUSTLING)

31:58.918 --> 32:02.042
(FOOTSTEPS)

32:06.501 --> 32:10.167
- You know, I'm really
reluctant to ask

32:10.209 --> 32:13.459
but it is very important.

32:13.501 --> 32:14.792
- What, Ben?

32:14.834 --> 32:16.810
- You left my coconut water
on the porch yesterday.

32:16.834 --> 32:19.250
Now it is ruined.

32:19.292 --> 32:20.393
- You have got to be kidding me.

32:20.417 --> 32:23.042
You simply take the
left side waters

32:23.083 --> 32:24.958
and move some over to the...

32:24.959 --> 32:27.626
Is this a game?

32:27.667 --> 32:29.792
Are you playing a game now?

32:29.834 --> 32:31.959
- What have you done?

32:32.042 --> 32:33.667
You've moved my water.

32:33.709 --> 32:35.125
(SIGH)
- I haven't touched

32:35.167 --> 32:36.250
your stupid water.

32:36.292 --> 32:37.626
Why would I touch your water?

32:37.667 --> 32:38.976
- So you wouldn't have
to go back and get more.

32:39.000 --> 32:41.000
- You know, I don't have
the energy for this today.

32:46.959 --> 32:50.125
(QUIET SQUEAL)

33:12.959 --> 33:16.626
(RUSTLING LEAVES)
(GLOOMY MUSIC)

33:20.959 --> 33:24.167
- I think we should talk
about our situation.

33:24.209 --> 33:26.958
- I'm done discussing
coconut water.

33:26.959 --> 33:29.958
- No, not that.

33:29.959 --> 33:31.209
I mean, our living situation.

33:31.667 --> 33:35.334
Well, you've been
here for two weeks

33:35.375 --> 33:38.417
and I don't feel like
you're making an effort.

33:38.459 --> 33:41.125
- Oh, really?

33:41.167 --> 33:42.584
- Wait.

33:42.626 --> 33:43.792
I have more.

33:43.834 --> 33:45.792
First, you mock me

33:45.834 --> 33:47.626
and you treat me like a child

33:47.667 --> 33:49.584
and then you make me beg

33:49.626 --> 33:50.810
for what little
help you do give.

33:50.834 --> 33:52.709
I need you here for me.

33:52.751 --> 33:54.310
And sometimes you're
just plain hateful.

33:54.334 --> 33:56.958
- Not trying?

33:56.959 --> 33:58.709
Take a look in the mirror.

33:58.751 --> 34:00.958
Hateful, sometimes

34:00.959 --> 34:03.250
but you're ungrateful and lazy.

34:03.501 --> 34:07.375
You know, since you won't
accept any real help

34:07.417 --> 34:08.792
from me anyway,

34:08.833 --> 34:09.958
maybe you just don't
need anyone here at all.

34:09.958 --> 34:11.958
So, believe me, as soon as
Duke's better, we're gone.

34:11.958 --> 34:14.876
- Wait.

34:14.918 --> 34:16.958
I don't want that.

34:17.000 --> 34:19.876
I'm sorry.

34:19.918 --> 34:21.958
Let's just try to treat
each other better.

34:21.958 --> 34:24.125
Can we agree on that?

34:25.000 --> 34:28.250
- Sure.

34:28.708 --> 34:32.333
Look, I need to
tell you something.

34:32.375 --> 34:35.876
Ben, I think you're
getting worse.

34:35.918 --> 34:39.042
I called a colleague
of mine, Dr. Thompson,

34:39.083 --> 34:41.458
to come out...

34:41.501 --> 34:42.208
- No!

34:42.250 --> 34:43.333
I'm not the crazy one.

34:43.375 --> 34:44.958
Call him and tell
him not to come.

34:44.958 --> 34:46.333
- It's too late.

34:46.375 --> 34:47.935
- Well, when he gets here than
I'll just throw him out...

34:47.958 --> 34:50.250
- What is it?

34:50.292 --> 34:52.833
- Nothing, there's
just a pretty girl

34:52.876 --> 34:55.792
standing in the doorway.

34:55.833 --> 34:57.958
- No there isn't.

34:57.959 --> 35:00.209
That's the doctor you're
gonna throw out on her ass.

35:00.459 --> 35:03.626
Hi.

35:03.667 --> 35:04.334
- Hi, how are you?

35:04.375 --> 35:06.101
So good to see you.
- [STACEY] Oh my, goodness.

35:06.125 --> 35:07.209
Come in.

35:07.250 --> 35:07.959
- Thanks.

35:08.000 --> 35:10.626
And you must be Ben.

35:10.667 --> 35:12.459
How are you?

35:12.501 --> 35:13.876
- I'm uh...

35:13.918 --> 35:15.101
- OK, we'll come
back to you later.

35:15.125 --> 35:17.626
- Cool house.

35:17.667 --> 35:19.584
- It was a boarding
school for girls.

35:19.626 --> 35:21.375
- Hmm.
- [BEN] It closed in 1919

35:21.417 --> 35:22.959
when the headmistress
hanged herself.

35:23.042 --> 35:24.834
- Ew, and you grew up here?

35:24.876 --> 35:26.459
- She didn't do it in the house.

35:28.959 --> 35:32.709
- Your brother seems so sweet.

35:32.751 --> 35:34.459
- Yech, don't let him
fool you, he's crazy.

35:34.501 --> 35:37.876
- Crazy cute.
- [STACEY] Mmm...

35:37.918 --> 35:39.501
(RIP)
(SCREAM)

35:41.959 --> 35:45.250
- Everything OK in here?

35:45.292 --> 35:47.125
- Look.

35:47.167 --> 35:47.959
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

35:47.960 --> 35:48.976
Somebody should check that out.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.417
(SIGHS)
- I guess it's up to me.

35:53.959 --> 35:55.959
- I guess, I guess I could go.

35:57.626 --> 36:00.834
- [STACEY] Yeah, save it.

36:12.834 --> 36:15.958
God.

36:15.959 --> 36:17.959
(FOOTSTEPS)

36:21.709 --> 36:22.709
(SCEAM)
- Stacey!

36:25.000 --> 36:26.958
Are you alright?!

36:26.959 --> 36:27.959
(SCREAM)

36:28.000 --> 36:29.083
- Stacey!

36:29.125 --> 36:30.626
Please, say something!

36:30.667 --> 36:32.125
- It's a spider!

36:32.167 --> 36:34.042
I got it!

36:37.626 --> 36:40.959
That's weird.

36:43.209 --> 36:44.959
(PANTING)

36:46.542 --> 36:49.751
I don't see anything.

36:50.042 --> 36:52.417
(SIGH)
Sorry,

36:53.501 --> 36:54.375
I hate those little bastards.

36:54.417 --> 36:56.417
Anyway, there's
nothing up there.

36:56.459 --> 36:57.918
Not a speck.

36:57.959 --> 36:59.599
But I did find this
really weird painting.

37:00.083 --> 37:02.918
- I'm not staying in here.

37:03.751 --> 37:05.083
- There's always Mother's room.

37:05.125 --> 37:06.958
- That's where she died.

37:06.959 --> 37:08.459
- Pass.

37:08.501 --> 37:09.501
Anybody die on the couch?

37:12.959 --> 37:16.083
(CREEPY CHORAL MUSIC)

37:36.250 --> 37:39.959
- So, last night
was pretty strange.

37:40.959 --> 37:44.792
Does that sort of
thing happen a lot?

37:44.834 --> 37:46.834
- Not so much.

37:46.876 --> 37:48.501
- Your house is kind
of freaking me out.

37:48.542 --> 37:50.959
I did some research.

37:51.042 --> 37:54.958
They said that there
was a punishment room

37:54.959 --> 37:56.958
where the headmistress locked up

37:56.959 --> 37:59.417
the little girls for days.

37:59.459 --> 38:01.876
- Not likely.

38:01.918 --> 38:03.375
I know every inch of this house.

38:03.417 --> 38:06.292
One of the benefits
of being a shut-in.

38:06.334 --> 38:08.542
Wait a minute.

38:08.584 --> 38:11.584
That's her.

38:11.626 --> 38:13.709
Stacey, that's the girl
I saw petting Duke.

38:13.751 --> 38:17.209
Her hair is cut
up but that's her.

38:17.250 --> 38:20.083
See, she even has
the leg brace on.

38:20.125 --> 38:22.958
- That photo was
taken in 1919, so...

38:22.959 --> 38:26.375
- Third from the
left, Abbey Grace.

38:26.959 --> 38:30.958
Hey, isn't that one of the
names from your painting?

38:30.959 --> 38:33.667
- After they closed
this school, hmmm,

38:33.709 --> 38:36.334
it was sold as a
private residence

38:36.375 --> 38:38.292
where, in 1943,

38:38.584 --> 38:42.375
another little girl
slaughtered her family.

38:42.417 --> 38:45.292
- Any good news in there?

38:45.334 --> 38:47.626
- Not really.

38:47.667 --> 38:49.584
After she killed her family,

38:49.626 --> 38:51.959
she hung herself
from your oak tree.

38:52.042 --> 38:54.667
- Wow.

38:54.709 --> 38:55.375
- I don't get it.

38:55.417 --> 38:56.935
How does a child manage
to kill her whole family?

38:56.959 --> 38:59.959
- I don't know,
element of surprise?

39:00.000 --> 39:02.459
- I'm gonna go in town,
gonna go check on Duke.

39:02.501 --> 39:04.958
- You're going in to town?

39:04.959 --> 39:06.209
- [STACEY] Yeah.

39:06.250 --> 39:09.959
I'll get your coconut water.

39:14.167 --> 39:17.375
- Ben?

39:17.417 --> 39:20.209
I'd like to help you
with your issues.

39:21.083 --> 39:24.584
Would that be OK?

39:27.584 --> 39:28.584
Great.

39:30.959 --> 39:34.250
So, you said that touching
was a major challenge for you.

39:34.959 --> 39:38.417
Let's just jump in
with both hands.

39:39.501 --> 39:42.959
(GASPS)
Sorry, hold on.

39:44.167 --> 39:47.375
OK.

39:52.959 --> 39:56.709
So, when did it
all start for you?

39:56.918 --> 40:00.375
Like, what age do you think?

40:01.834 --> 40:04.959
See, it's good.

40:05.000 --> 40:07.209
It's good.

40:07.250 --> 40:09.542
Ben, you're doing so good.

40:09.584 --> 40:11.334
Are you ready to take
another step further?

40:11.375 --> 40:14.042
Ready?

40:14.083 --> 40:16.876
Good job.

40:16.918 --> 40:18.292
And we're just gonna take

40:18.334 --> 40:20.958
step.

40:20.959 --> 40:23.042
You know what?

40:23.083 --> 40:24.918
It's OK.

40:24.959 --> 40:28.626
It looks like rain, anyways.

40:31.834 --> 40:32.834
(BLOWING WIND)

40:38.417 --> 40:39.417
- Geez.
(WHOOSH)

40:41.876 --> 40:43.584
(SLAM)

40:43.626 --> 40:44.834
(THUD)

40:44.876 --> 40:46.959
(WHIMPERING)

40:47.042 --> 40:49.209
- Ow, ow ow.

40:56.959 --> 41:00.250
(PANICKED GASPING)

41:04.417 --> 41:05.417
Stacey.

41:07.667 --> 41:09.083
Stacey!

41:11.876 --> 41:12.876
Help me!

41:14.959 --> 41:17.250
I'm in the basement!

41:20.000 --> 41:21.375
Stacey!

41:23.709 --> 41:26.959
Bridget!

41:29.000 --> 41:30.918
I'm down here!

41:32.417 --> 41:34.958
Help!

41:34.959 --> 41:36.958
Please!

41:36.959 --> 41:38.709
Please!

41:38.751 --> 41:41.292
(PANTING)

41:50.667 --> 41:54.459
- What in the world are
you doing down here?

41:54.501 --> 41:55.958
- I fell.

41:55.959 --> 41:57.393
- [BRIDGET] Jesus,
Ben, are you alright?

41:57.417 --> 41:59.542
- I need a shower.

42:01.918 --> 42:03.834
- You need to check on him.

42:05.375 --> 42:06.584
(SIGHS)
- He's fine.

42:06.626 --> 42:08.626
Just a little dirty.

42:08.667 --> 42:09.810
Hell, it'll probably
do him some good.

42:09.834 --> 42:11.292
- Stacey.

42:11.334 --> 42:12.958
- You go, he'd rather
you check on him anyway.

42:12.959 --> 42:16.167
- Fine.

42:19.375 --> 42:22.542
Ben?

42:22.584 --> 42:23.876
Are you alright?

42:23.918 --> 42:25.209
I knocked but you didn't answer.

42:25.250 --> 42:28.876
- It's the craziest thing.

42:28.918 --> 42:30.678
I was reviewing the
footage from the basement

42:30.709 --> 42:33.667
and, well, let me just show you.

42:33.709 --> 42:36.125
- Footage?

42:36.167 --> 42:37.918
- Yes, Mother had
cameras put in.

42:38.709 --> 42:41.959
(CLICKING)

42:44.626 --> 42:46.501
I swear,

42:47.876 --> 42:49.876
I saw something reach from
the shadows and grab me.

42:59.167 --> 43:02.709
You believe me, right?

43:02.751 --> 43:04.709
- Of course I do.

43:04.751 --> 43:06.958
- I can't, I'm sorry, I can't.

43:06.959 --> 43:09.584
- No, you were traumatized.

43:09.626 --> 43:11.334
It was wrong of me.

43:22.959 --> 43:26.417
(UNSETTLING AIRY MUSIC)

43:51.042 --> 43:54.459
(THUD)
(SIGHS)

43:54.501 --> 43:56.375
- You're so stupid.

43:56.959 --> 44:00.042
So stupid.

44:00.083 --> 44:03.626
You're so stupid.

44:04.876 --> 44:07.959
(SIGHS)

44:17.542 --> 44:20.959
(MUFFLED, ANGUISHED CRIES)

44:24.751 --> 44:26.591
Stacey, is there something
wrong with your leg?

44:28.667 --> 44:31.959
(MUFFLED, ANGUISHED CRIES)

44:49.959 --> 44:53.501
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)
(GASPS)

45:02.209 --> 45:05.751
- What the Hell, Stacey?

45:05.792 --> 45:06.959
- You got to be kidding me.

45:07.000 --> 45:10.292
This is weird, even
for his standards.

45:11.667 --> 45:15.000
I can't even take this.

45:15.250 --> 45:18.584
- Calm down.

45:18.626 --> 45:19.768
We'll just put everything back.

45:19.792 --> 45:21.959
- Put what back?

45:22.042 --> 45:23.226
- This is too much,
Ben, even for you.

45:23.250 --> 45:25.876
- You really think I did this?

45:25.918 --> 45:27.626
- Who else?

45:27.667 --> 45:28.501
You stack shit everywhere.

45:28.542 --> 45:30.334
Everything's lines up
perfect and organized.

45:30.375 --> 45:32.792
I'm sure by some sort of
screwed-up logic of yours.

45:32.834 --> 45:35.501
- There must be a
simple explanation.

45:35.542 --> 45:38.459
You could have done it
without knowing, Ben.

45:38.501 --> 45:40.501
- Me?

45:40.542 --> 45:41.959
What about Stacey?

45:42.042 --> 45:43.876
She's trying to drive me crazy

45:43.918 --> 45:44.976
so she can write about
it in her stupid book.

45:45.000 --> 45:47.709
Yeah, I know about that.

45:47.751 --> 45:49.959
You should write about yourself.

45:50.000 --> 45:51.834
I'm not the one who
had the breakdown.

45:51.876 --> 45:54.083
- Stacey?

45:54.125 --> 45:55.000
- What happened when I was 17

45:55.042 --> 45:56.876
has nothing to do
with this, Ben.

45:56.918 --> 45:59.459
You're just messing with me.

45:59.501 --> 46:01.667
- The video.

46:01.709 --> 46:03.709
We can watch the video.

46:03.918 --> 46:06.417
(CLICKING)

46:09.501 --> 46:11.792
(SNARL)

46:12.751 --> 46:13.958
- Holy shit, what
the Hell was that?

46:13.959 --> 46:16.042
- It's Abbey Grace, look.

46:16.083 --> 46:19.501
- Back it up.

46:23.250 --> 46:26.751
- You saw it, right?

46:26.792 --> 46:27.417
- Yes.

46:27.459 --> 46:28.209
- Stacey, you too?

46:28.250 --> 46:29.958
- Yeah, right, Ben,
this isn't funny.

46:29.959 --> 46:31.834
I don't know how you did that.

46:31.876 --> 46:33.959
Stop screwing with me.

46:34.042 --> 46:35.876
- I did nothing.

46:35.918 --> 46:36.959
- Come on, guys.

46:37.042 --> 46:38.792
Stacey!

46:43.626 --> 46:46.958
- He rigged it somehow.

46:46.959 --> 46:49.958
Just to get attention.

46:49.959 --> 46:51.958
- I believe him.

46:51.959 --> 46:52.959
- What?

46:53.000 --> 46:54.876
- I'm not saying
that he didn't do it

46:54.918 --> 46:56.685
but maybe he just doesn't
know that he did it.

46:56.709 --> 46:59.959
- Well, either way,

47:00.000 --> 47:01.958
I just can't do it anymore.

47:01.959 --> 47:04.375
When Duke's better, I'm just
gonna put him in a facility

47:04.417 --> 47:07.459
and sell the house.

47:07.501 --> 47:09.667
- He's all the
family that you have.

47:09.709 --> 47:11.334
Just don't make
any rash decisions.

47:12.250 --> 47:15.584
What if...?

47:15.626 --> 47:17.042
- What?

47:17.083 --> 47:19.501
- What if he didn't do it?

47:19.542 --> 47:22.083
How would you explain it?

47:22.125 --> 47:24.959
- I don't know,
what do you think?

47:25.125 --> 47:28.792
- Maybe we have some kind of

47:28.834 --> 47:30.959
OCD poltergeist on our hands.

47:31.417 --> 47:34.959
- So, you think my
mother came back

47:35.042 --> 47:36.334
and rearranged the kitchen?

47:36.375 --> 47:37.958
(LAUGHS)
- Maybe.

47:37.959 --> 47:40.959
I'm gonna go inside.

47:41.000 --> 47:42.292
You coming?

47:42.334 --> 47:43.958
- Yeah, soon.

47:43.959 --> 47:44.959
- [BRIDGET] OK.

47:46.959 --> 47:47.959
(PLINKY MUSIC BOX)

47:54.250 --> 47:55.334
- How did you get out here?

48:00.083 --> 48:01.876
(EERIE MUSIC)

48:08.542 --> 48:11.959
(DRIPPING WATER)

48:23.000 --> 48:26.209
(ROAR)

48:26.250 --> 48:28.959
(HEAVY DRUMBEATS)

48:32.042 --> 48:33.209
(GASPING)

48:38.667 --> 48:40.209
(COUGHING)

48:44.042 --> 48:45.042
(SIGHS)

48:47.292 --> 48:48.876
How was your bath?

48:48.918 --> 48:50.334
(CRYING)

48:50.375 --> 48:52.876
Are you alright?

48:53.125 --> 48:56.292
OK.

48:56.334 --> 48:57.626
(SOBBING)

48:57.667 --> 48:59.709
OK.

49:00.083 --> 49:03.959
- It was like, something
pulled me under

49:04.876 --> 49:08.626
and Ben said that
something grabbed him

49:08.667 --> 49:10.292
and pulled him in
to the basement.

49:11.876 --> 49:13.959
What is it?

49:15.000 --> 49:17.042
- I thought I saw Duke's
reflection in the mirror

49:17.083 --> 49:18.958
the other night.

49:18.959 --> 49:19.959
I just dismissed it.

49:20.000 --> 49:22.584
I just thought I was tired.

49:22.626 --> 49:25.958
- I know a guy,
his name is Roman,

49:25.959 --> 49:28.876
he's like a spiritualist.

49:28.918 --> 49:30.959
I can call him.

49:31.042 --> 49:31.959
- I don't know.

49:32.000 --> 49:33.685
I don't think Ben would let
anybody else in the house.

49:33.709 --> 49:36.209
- But think about it.

49:36.250 --> 49:37.209
Weird things are happening.

49:37.250 --> 49:38.894
Duke, he's like the
sweetest dog I've ever met

49:38.918 --> 49:41.834
and he tried to kill you.

49:41.876 --> 49:43.810
- I know but the vet said
it could have been Xanax,

49:43.834 --> 49:45.876
a reaction to it or there
could be some bacteria

49:45.918 --> 49:48.167
in the system or something.

49:48.209 --> 49:49.375
I just...

49:49.417 --> 49:50.876
- Maybe it was but
what if it wasn't?

49:53.959 --> 49:55.042
(KNOCKING)

49:57.292 --> 49:58.959
- Yeah?

49:59.125 --> 50:02.501
- Can I come in?

50:02.542 --> 50:04.083
- Alright, sure.

50:04.125 --> 50:07.751
- I'm sorry about earlier.

50:07.792 --> 50:09.501
- We all are.

50:09.542 --> 50:11.125
Tell him, Stacey.

50:12.792 --> 50:15.958
(SIGHS)

50:15.959 --> 50:18.792
I'll call him now.

50:18.834 --> 50:19.958
- You can use my phone.

50:19.959 --> 50:21.459
It's the only land-line we have.

50:32.209 --> 50:35.876
(MUFFLED, ANGUISHED CRIES)

51:09.042 --> 51:12.709
(INTENSE DISCORDANT MUSIC)

51:20.042 --> 51:23.417
(ROARING SCREAM)

51:23.459 --> 51:24.959
- OK, I'll pick you
up at the airport.

51:25.584 --> 51:27.959
And Roman, thanks again.

51:29.501 --> 51:31.876
- I hope this works.

51:32.959 --> 51:33.751
- Yeah.

51:33.792 --> 51:35.417
(SIMULTANEOUS SCEAMS)

51:35.459 --> 51:36.959
- What the Hell, Bridget?

51:37.042 --> 51:38.958
- Stacey.

51:38.959 --> 51:40.834
(CREAKING)

51:41.834 --> 51:45.000
(CREEPY MUSIC)

51:49.792 --> 51:53.083
(HOBBLING FOOTSTEPS)

51:55.584 --> 51:57.959
(MUFFLED, ANGUISHED CRIES)

52:04.959 --> 52:08.417
(HOBBLING FOOTSTEPS)

52:18.834 --> 52:21.959
(SLAM)

52:24.959 --> 52:25.959
(CAR ENGINE)

52:35.334 --> 52:38.834
- Are you coming in?

52:38.876 --> 52:41.042
- In a minute.

52:42.876 --> 52:43.918
(SLURPING)

52:45.959 --> 52:47.375
- Hey, guys.

52:53.000 --> 52:56.542
- [BEN] What's he doing?

52:56.584 --> 52:57.959
- He said to give him a minute.

52:58.000 --> 53:00.792
(KNOCKING)

53:06.000 --> 53:09.292
Anything?

53:09.334 --> 53:10.375
- In a minute.

53:13.125 --> 53:16.751
From what you've told me,

53:16.792 --> 53:17.935
I think you have
a restless spirit.

53:17.959 --> 53:19.918
- A demon?

53:19.959 --> 53:21.143
- No, a demon is a
whole different story.

53:21.167 --> 53:24.959
A spirit is usually
just looking to move on.

53:25.000 --> 53:27.959
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)
- Move on?

53:28.000 --> 53:29.958
- To the afterlife.

53:29.959 --> 53:32.083
When we die, one of
three things happens.

53:32.125 --> 53:35.501
Our souls go to Heaven or Hell.

53:35.542 --> 53:38.292
Sometimes something
holds us here.

53:38.334 --> 53:41.667
It's very very rare.

53:41.709 --> 53:43.958
A spirit becomes violent

53:43.959 --> 53:46.083
or even able to enter
the human realm again.

53:46.250 --> 53:49.876
- But, if that's the case,

53:49.918 --> 53:51.250
why did it push
me down the steps?

53:51.292 --> 53:53.292
- And me in the tub?

53:53.334 --> 53:55.834
- Rare, but not impossible.

53:55.876 --> 53:58.958
There had to be
evil and violence

53:58.959 --> 54:01.250
that contributed to their death.

54:01.292 --> 54:03.667
A touch of darkness enters
their soul and drops it here.

54:06.334 --> 54:08.709
It's consumed by evil
and wreaks vengeance

54:10.167 --> 54:13.083
on anyone it can connect to.

54:16.959 --> 54:20.083
(GAGS AND SNIFFS)
(INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

54:35.542 --> 54:38.834
- Stacey?

54:38.876 --> 54:39.667
- It's OK.

54:39.709 --> 54:41.959
Everyone has their own beliefs.

54:42.083 --> 54:45.751
- Do we have a problem here?

54:45.792 --> 54:47.292
- Not sure.

54:47.334 --> 54:49.667
I'd love to look around, see
if I can determine what it is.

54:49.918 --> 54:53.042
- Can we help?

54:53.083 --> 54:54.542
- No, just give me
a couple of hours.

54:54.709 --> 54:58.417
- But what if it is
a vengeful spirit?

54:58.459 --> 55:01.918
- Let's pray not.

55:01.959 --> 55:04.417
(INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

55:04.459 --> 55:07.375
(CREAK)

55:19.626 --> 55:22.959
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

55:28.417 --> 55:32.250
I'm gonna need my holy
water for this one.

55:33.959 --> 55:37.209
Goddamn it.

55:38.334 --> 55:41.959
- Not a very promising start.

55:45.042 --> 55:48.792
- I need someone
to go into town.

55:48.834 --> 55:50.125
- I'll do it.

55:50.167 --> 55:51.918
- Take this luck
charge of the sacrament

55:51.959 --> 55:53.584
and fill it with holy water.

55:53.626 --> 55:55.209
- OK.

55:57.959 --> 56:01.334
(CRUNCHY FOOTSTEPS)

56:15.083 --> 56:18.584
(THUNDEROUS CRASH)

56:20.959 --> 56:22.959
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

56:29.375 --> 56:33.250
- I wonder where little
girls go when they die.

56:36.334 --> 56:37.959
(SNAP)

56:41.417 --> 56:42.417
(CRUNCHY FOOTSTEPS)

56:49.667 --> 56:52.958
(HEAVY BREATHING)

56:52.959 --> 56:55.958
- You OK?

56:55.959 --> 56:57.709
- I need to be alone.

56:57.751 --> 56:59.042
- What's going on?

56:59.083 --> 57:00.751
- Out!

57:00.792 --> 57:02.375
Now!

57:07.375 --> 57:10.918
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

57:17.834 --> 57:21.417
Bless this home
and all who enter.

57:21.459 --> 57:24.626
Please cleanse this
home of all stagnant

57:24.667 --> 57:26.959
and negative energy.

57:27.000 --> 57:29.250
Fill this home with light, love,

57:29.292 --> 57:32.167
and with positive energy
of the highest vibration.

57:32.209 --> 57:35.751
(RUMBLING THUD)

57:36.042 --> 57:39.542
Bless this home
and all who enter.

57:39.918 --> 57:42.876
Please cleanse this
home of all stagnant

57:42.918 --> 57:45.959
and negative energy.

57:47.959 --> 57:49.959
Home with light and love

57:51.542 --> 57:53.393
and with positive energy
of the highest vibration.

57:53.417 --> 57:56.209
(WHOOSH)

57:56.918 --> 57:59.959
(SLAM)

58:00.417 --> 58:03.834
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

58:03.959 --> 58:07.459
(SHUFFLING STEPS)

58:12.250 --> 58:15.792
(SCREECHING SCREAMS)

58:24.792 --> 58:27.959
- What's going on?

58:28.042 --> 58:29.560
- You've got some serious
shit going on here, man.

58:29.584 --> 58:31.709
I tried but I can't help.

58:31.751 --> 58:34.292
- What do you mean?

58:34.334 --> 58:35.958
- You need to get out.

58:35.959 --> 58:37.667
- I don't get out.

58:37.709 --> 58:40.375
I don't get out.

58:40.417 --> 58:41.751
- Calm down, Ben.

58:41.792 --> 58:44.626
That's not an option.

58:44.667 --> 58:46.584
- Listen to me, for
your own safety,

58:46.626 --> 58:49.334
you need to get
the Hell out, now!

58:49.542 --> 58:53.250
I'm calling a cab
and I'm out of here.

58:53.292 --> 58:55.959
- No!

58:56.042 --> 58:57.459
- It's OK now.

58:57.501 --> 58:59.083
I'm never gonna leave you again.

58:59.125 --> 59:02.167
We'll never leave this place.

59:02.209 --> 59:03.876
(CREEPY MUSIC)

59:07.584 --> 59:08.584
(METALLIC RATTLE)

59:11.959 --> 59:15.209
(BEEPING)

59:17.918 --> 59:19.042
(RATTLING)

59:21.000 --> 59:23.958
- And hurry.

59:23.959 --> 59:26.959
(INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

59:27.918 --> 59:31.042
(PANICKED GROAN)

59:31.083 --> 59:34.167
- Why was Roman's bag outside?

59:34.209 --> 59:35.958
- [BEN] We've got problems.

59:35.959 --> 59:37.375
- Roman's gone.

59:37.417 --> 59:38.501
- What do you mean, gone?

59:38.542 --> 59:39.810
- I don't know, he said
he was calling a cab.

59:39.834 --> 59:42.059
- He wouldn't have just left
his bag out there, would he?

59:42.083 --> 59:44.626
- Maybe he's still around.

59:44.667 --> 59:46.834
- We should look for him.

59:46.876 --> 59:47.959
Maybe he changed his mind.

59:48.042 --> 59:50.334
- Yeah, Stacey and I
can go look outside.

59:50.584 --> 59:54.209
- You just stay
and look in here.

01:00:01.083 --> 01:00:04.417
- Roman?!

01:00:05.959 --> 01:00:09.209
Roman?!

01:00:09.501 --> 01:00:12.959
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:00:13.667 --> 01:00:16.876
- Roman?

01:00:16.918 --> 01:00:19.250
Roman?

01:00:19.292 --> 01:00:21.751
Roman?

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:29.542
Roman, are you here?

01:00:35.459 --> 01:00:38.667
(GASPS)

01:00:38.709 --> 01:00:39.918
Crap!

01:00:39.959 --> 01:00:41.459
- You wanna go out and play?

01:00:41.501 --> 01:00:43.542
- What?

01:00:51.167 --> 01:00:54.876
- Maybe he just forgot his bag

01:00:54.918 --> 01:00:56.958
and got the Hell out.

01:00:56.959 --> 01:00:58.918
(HEAVY BREATHING)
Stacey?

01:00:58.959 --> 01:01:01.792
Stacey.
(BREATHY ROAR)

01:01:01.834 --> 01:01:03.209
(THUD)
(GASP)

01:01:04.751 --> 01:01:06.375
- What the Hell?

01:01:07.959 --> 01:01:10.083
- You shouldn't take things
that don't belong to you.

01:01:11.959 --> 01:01:13.667
(ROARING SCREAM)

01:01:33.834 --> 01:01:36.959
- There!

01:01:38.292 --> 01:01:40.083
(EERIE MUSIC)

01:01:41.709 --> 01:01:44.667
- Holy shit.

01:01:44.709 --> 01:01:46.375
Shit, shit!

01:01:46.417 --> 01:01:48.542
Where is she, where is she?

01:01:49.125 --> 01:01:52.584
Ben, where is she?

01:01:52.626 --> 01:01:54.958
(SLAM)
(SNARLING)

01:01:54.959 --> 01:01:56.501
Stacey, please stop it!

01:01:56.542 --> 01:01:58.958
(THUD)

01:01:58.959 --> 01:02:01.125
(BANGING)
What are we gonna do?

01:02:01.167 --> 01:02:03.792
- Let me think, let me think.

01:02:03.834 --> 01:02:05.958
(BANGING)
It's still Stacey

01:02:05.959 --> 01:02:07.083
so we can't hurt her.

01:02:07.125 --> 01:02:10.167
We just need to
subdue her somehow.

01:02:10.209 --> 01:02:12.958
(CRASH)

01:02:12.959 --> 01:02:15.959
(WHIMPERING)

01:02:18.959 --> 01:02:19.959
(CREAK)

01:02:25.959 --> 01:02:27.167
(HOBBLING FOOTSTEPS)

01:02:30.959 --> 01:02:33.958
- No.

01:02:33.959 --> 01:02:36.042
(CLUNK)
(THUD)

01:02:39.459 --> 01:02:42.667
- You said subdue
her, not kill her.

01:02:42.709 --> 01:02:45.292
- Check her.

01:02:45.334 --> 01:02:46.334
- You check her.

01:02:53.709 --> 01:02:56.958
- She's alive.

01:02:56.959 --> 01:02:58.958
Help me tie her up.

01:02:58.959 --> 01:03:00.375
(HEAVY PANTING)

01:03:02.042 --> 01:03:03.959
Line is dead.

01:03:08.292 --> 01:03:09.292
Anything?

01:03:11.626 --> 01:03:12.792
- Battery's dead.

01:03:12.834 --> 01:03:14.667
I've got a quick-charge
adapter in my purse.

01:03:14.959 --> 01:03:17.958
Shit!

01:03:17.959 --> 01:03:19.958
- What?

01:03:19.959 --> 01:03:20.976
- I left it in Stacey's car.

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:23.959
I'll go get it.

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:25.667
(GROANING)

01:03:26.292 --> 01:03:29.501
Stacey?

01:03:29.542 --> 01:03:30.751
- Stacey,

01:03:30.792 --> 01:03:32.459
how do you feel?

01:03:32.876 --> 01:03:35.959
(GUTTURAL CHOMP)

01:03:36.042 --> 01:03:37.751
(YELL)
(INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:03:37.792 --> 01:03:40.876
(GUTTURAL ROARS)

01:03:53.459 --> 01:03:56.667
(RIP)

01:03:56.709 --> 01:03:59.958
(CRASH)

01:03:59.959 --> 01:04:01.792
- Things that belong
to me were taken!

01:04:02.959 --> 01:04:06.626
Now I take something of yours!

01:04:09.292 --> 01:04:11.000
(SCREAMING)

01:04:16.709 --> 01:04:17.709
- Run!

01:04:19.959 --> 01:04:22.209
(THUNDEROUS DRUMMING MUSIC)

01:04:22.375 --> 01:04:25.792
(GUTTURAL ROARS)

01:04:35.501 --> 01:04:38.876
- Come on, Ben.

01:04:38.918 --> 01:04:40.292
Come on, we gotta go.

01:04:40.334 --> 01:04:41.959
- He's not.

01:04:42.626 --> 01:04:46.125
I'll be back for you, brother.

01:04:47.959 --> 01:04:49.083
(RATTLING)

01:04:54.626 --> 01:04:55.626
(BEEPING)

01:04:57.959 --> 01:05:01.042
- Oh, my gosh.

01:05:07.751 --> 01:05:11.292
(GROWLING)
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

01:05:18.959 --> 01:05:22.042
(ROAR)

01:05:23.292 --> 01:05:26.709
(ROARING SCREAM)

01:05:29.292 --> 01:05:30.959
- You know I never
really liked you.

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:36.334
(CRUNCH)

01:05:36.375 --> 01:05:37.959
- Listen, bitch,

01:05:38.042 --> 01:05:39.459
now you let go of
my best friend.

01:05:39.501 --> 01:05:41.584
So just get the fuck out of her!

01:05:43.959 --> 01:05:45.125
(HEAVY BREATHING)

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:52.000
(CREAKING)

01:05:54.334 --> 01:05:56.959
(BUZZING)

01:06:04.959 --> 01:06:08.083
(GASPS)

01:06:08.125 --> 01:06:08.959
(SLAM)

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:11.417
(THUMPING)

01:06:11.459 --> 01:06:14.792
- Let me out, let me out.

01:06:24.792 --> 01:06:27.959
(RUSTLING)

01:06:28.375 --> 01:06:31.876
(PLINKY MUSIC BOX)

01:06:44.250 --> 01:06:48.042
- Are you ready to
tell me where it is?!

01:06:57.167 --> 01:07:00.709
I know you've got it.

01:07:00.751 --> 01:07:02.834
I heard it.

01:07:05.459 --> 01:07:08.792
Little girls

01:07:08.834 --> 01:07:11.042
who lie

01:07:11.083 --> 01:07:12.459
don't

01:07:12.501 --> 01:07:13.751
get in

01:07:13.792 --> 01:07:14.834
to Heaven!

01:07:19.959 --> 01:07:23.375
I'll find it myself.

01:07:33.459 --> 01:07:36.709
(RATTLE)

01:07:39.667 --> 01:07:42.959
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:07:48.667 --> 01:07:51.958
(BUZZING)

01:07:51.959 --> 01:07:54.958
(THUMPING)

01:07:54.959 --> 01:07:58.626
(HEAVY PANTING AND WHIMPERING)

01:08:11.959 --> 01:08:15.083
- Abbey Grace!

01:08:15.125 --> 01:08:18.292
I know you're a good girl!

01:08:18.334 --> 01:08:21.709
I know what it's
like to be trapped!

01:08:21.959 --> 01:08:25.501
Maybe we can help each other!

01:08:25.709 --> 01:08:28.957
Come to me!

01:08:28.959 --> 01:08:30.501
Come on!

01:08:30.542 --> 01:08:32.292
We can be friends.

01:08:32.334 --> 01:08:33.876
(SCRAPING)

01:08:33.917 --> 01:08:36.501
Tell me what you want!

01:08:40.959 --> 01:08:44.042
- Shhh.

01:08:45.959 --> 01:08:46.959
- Damn it!

01:08:49.042 --> 01:08:50.334
(INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:09:03.501 --> 01:09:06.792
That's it.

01:09:06.834 --> 01:09:08.626
(HEAVY BREATHING)

01:09:35.959 --> 01:09:39.459
(BLOOD-CURDLING SCREAM)

01:09:41.626 --> 01:09:44.082
(SLAM)
(THUD)

01:09:44.959 --> 01:09:47.959
- I've got it.

01:09:48.042 --> 01:09:49.292
I know what happened to you.

01:09:49.334 --> 01:09:50.584
I know what you want.

01:09:50.626 --> 01:09:52.876
- You only know what
I allow you to know!

01:09:52.959 --> 01:09:56.626
See what I allow you to see!

01:09:56.959 --> 01:10:00.501
- Please, leave my sister alone.

01:10:00.542 --> 01:10:03.167
(GUTTURAL GROANS)

01:10:04.334 --> 01:10:07.501
No!

01:10:07.542 --> 01:10:08.375
(CRUNCH)
Ahh, stop it!

01:10:08.417 --> 01:10:11.542
- Don't worry.

01:10:11.584 --> 01:10:14.167
When I'm through
with this night,

01:10:14.209 --> 01:10:16.292
she will join you.

01:10:16.334 --> 01:10:18.584
(HISSING)

